    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCame across a case where `vim.notify(..., vim.log.levels.ERROR)` throws an error.\n\nNeovim reports the following error using the reproduction steps:\n```\nError in /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:\nE5113: Lua chunk: /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:31: Vim:Lua :command callback: Vim:Exit code: 1\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'wait'\n        /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:20: in function 'wait_for_exit_code'\n        /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:28: in function </tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:26>\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_cmd'\n        /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:31: in main chunk\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_cmd'\n        /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:31: in main chunk\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nRun `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua` where `minimal.lua` is the following:\n\n```lua\n_G.Bug = {}\n\nBug.exit_code = nil\nBug.skip_wait = false\n\nfunction Bug.run_job()\n  Bug.exit_code = nil\n\n  vim.fn.jobstart('exit 1', {\n    on_exit = function(_, exit_code)\n      Bug.exit_code = exit_code\n      vim.schedule(function()\n        -- NOTE: Swapping vim.log.levels.INFO with vim.log.levels.ERROR does not cause an error\n        vim.notify('Exit code: ' .. exit_code, vim.log.levels.ERROR)\n      end)\n    end,\n  })\nend\n\nfunction Bug.wait_for_exit_code()\n  vim.fn.wait(1000, function()\n    return Bug.skip_wait or Bug.exit_code ~= nil\n  end)\n  vim.notify('Done', vim.log.levels.INFO)\nend\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command('Bug', function()\n  Bug.run_job()\n  Bug.wait_for_exit_code()\nend, {})\n\nvim.api.nvim_cmd({ cmd = 'Bug' }, {})\n```\nYou should get the same error after running the command again.\n\nNote that if you set the flag to skip waiting:\n```lua\n:lua Bug.skip_wait = true\n```\nThen you'll get the expected behavior when you run the `:Bug` command where no error is thrown and just a red \"Exit code: 1\" is printed after the job finishes.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect `vim.notify(..., vim.log.levels.ERROR)` to always just print a red notification message\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-509+g1813e1c089\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04 LTS (WSL)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNU bash, version 5.2.21\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
