            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Just to clarify. The \"error\" in the echoerr sense is what I would expect, but it appears to be throwing an actual `error()` given the circumstances created in the `minimal.lua`.\n\nIf I comment out the wait\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command('Bug', function()\n  Bug.run_job()\n  -- Bug.wait_for_exit_code()\nend, {})\n```\nthen vim just prints a red:\n```\nExit code: 1\n```\n\nLeaving it in, however, appears to cause an error in the error() sense:\n```\nError in /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:\nE5113: Lua chunk: /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:34: Vim:Lua :command callback: Vim:Exit code: 1\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'wait'\n        /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:23: in function 'wait_for_exit_code'\n        /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:31: in function </tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:29>\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_cmd'\n        /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:34: in main chunk\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_cmd'\n        /tmp/bug/minimal-2.lua:34: in main chunk\n```",
