            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "so according to : https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7d99104058fd2653903830c2b39b42d80092e646/test/functional/api/vim_spec.lua#L449-L454 if you call nvim_echo with err=1 and inside pcall (if trylevel>0) then we expect it to throw error. since \nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7d99104058fd2653903830c2b39b42d80092e646/runtime/lua/vim/_core/editor.lua#L683-L690 calls err=1 if you call it with `level == vim.log.levels.ERROR`. since inside the jobstart the trylevel is > 0 (i checked its 2) thats why it results in throwing error. i dont properly know the codebase so i dont know if its intentional or not. \n\nAdditional info if somebody want to fix:\nnvim_echo evantually calls `emsg_multiline` function which calls to cause_errthrow \nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7d99104058fd2653903830c2b39b42d80092e646/src/nvim/message.c#L798 \nwhich has this condition  \nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7d99104058fd2653903830c2b39b42d80092e646/src/nvim/ex_eval.c#L189 ",
